My only complaint was that at 2300h, you have to ring to get buzzed into the foyer, and its a bit nippy to stand waiting for the night manager to let you in.	My only real complaint was the food at the hotel...it wasnt the tastiest, and wasnt good value for the money, i would suggest eating at one of the many restaurants outside of the hotel.	My other complaint is that one cannot open the windows, which is usually a no-go for me.	My only actual complaint is that the bed had to be the most uncomfortable I've ever slept in.